cat << EOF
VLC (initially VideoLAN Client) is a highly portable multimedia player for
various audio and video formats (MPEG-1, MPEG-2, MPEG-4, DivX, mp3, ogg, ...)
as well as DVDs, VCDs, and various streaming protocols. It can also be used as
a server to stream in unicast or multicast in IPv4 or IPv6 on a high-bandwidth
network. 
